latestPosts.caption:
paris gave me laughter, companionship, inspiration. a trip that felt like pages from a journal i didn’t know i was writing—soft and saturated, filled with laughter echoing through narrow streets and the hush of galleries that felt like cathedrals. i spent the time with my five friends, our days unraveling in long walks, dizzy nights, and slow mornings where the city held us gently in its rhythm. but i also carved out time alone—because wandering solo, stepping into quiet rooms humming with creativity, has always been how i listen closest to a city’s voice.

i searched for a space that understood my love for design and architecture not as separate things, but as a shared language. that’s how i found @scenersgallery and the visit felt like entering a question, mid-thought. each piece—deliberate, tender—held a story in its shape. here, material becomes memory, and what’s unseen feels just as present as what’s before you.
